        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 6:04PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 603 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cass City, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Argyle around 610 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Parisville, McGregor,
Wilmot, White Rock, Snover, New Greenleaf, Ruth, Tyre, Decker, and
Palms.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
